	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok the quest starts at Rivervale in the Druid Farm. (Love that place)<BR>
Go here and Hail Shakey the Scarecrow. Ask Reebo what is wrong with Shakey. He will tell you Shakey needs stuffing and a head, but as I mentioned, you really don't need to chat with Reebo anymore to proceed with the<BR>
quest.<BR>
<BR>
Go to West Karana. There where the Scarecrows spawn you will find the Miller farm. You must get the no drop hay from the ground. You need one hay to continue the quest. <BR>
<BR>
After you have obtained the hay go speak with Priestess Jahnda in the Temple of Life in Qeynos. Tell here, &quot;I need the blessed oil for Estle&quot;. She will direct you to another priest who's name has slipped my mind. This priest gives the oil out. Ok so now you have the hay and the Blessed oil.<BR>
<BR>
Make sure ya have 66gold and head to the Ferrott. Might want to use invis on this one depending on your level. Look around the Cazic-Thule Temple entrance for an NPC Lizardman named Roror. Hail him then tell him, &quot;bless my hay&quot;. Give him the 66gold and the hay and he will return to you some cursed hay and some experience back.<BR>
<BR>
Now finally go back to Rivervale, in the Druid farm is a forge. Put the cursed hay and the blessed oil into the forge and combine it. You should get some Writhing Hay. (It looks like a pouch, ?!?) Ok give the writhing pouch...er hay to Shakey the Scarecrow and walla! You either get a neato magic weapon or a real nice magic belt for halflings. Repeat the quest as many times as you like to get both. Or more for a nice profit. The stats for each are Below. (lows 20s+ quest)<BR>
<BR>
WEE HARVESTER<BR>
Magic Item Lore Item<BR>
Skill: 2H Blunt  Atk Delay: 45<BR>
DMG: 10<BR>
STR +1  STA: +1  WIS: +3<BR>
Effect: Summon Food<BR>
WT: 6.0<BR>
Class: DRU<BR>
Race: HUM ELF HEF HFL<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
Well what can I say eheh, its a shovel. It gives<BR>
a lighting effect similar to a lightstone and the Summon<BR>
Food effect is 50 charges<BR>
<BR>
BELT OF THE RIVER<BR>
Magic Item Lore Item<BR>
Charges: 17<BR>
AC: 5<BR>
STR: +5  STA: +5  SV COLD: -10<BR>
Effect: Summon Drink<BR>
WT: 0.2<BR>
Class: WAR CLR DRU ROG<BR>
Race: HFL<BR>
<BR>
Notes:<BR>
Well it looks like a cloth belt. Its<BR>
only for halflings and it takes away<BR>
your save on cold but damn its neato!<BR>
<BR>
Palason <BR>
Wood-Elf<BR>
Druid<BR>
Bertuxxolous server<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

